title: S.F. building standoff ends — suspect arrested
text:
Photo: San Francisco Police Department Police outside a building at 10th and Harrison streets in San Francisco, where a suspected car thief was reportedly threatening to jump. Police outside a building at 10th and Harrison streets in San...
A 3½-hour standoff that shut down a busy South of Market street Wednesday ended when a suspected car thief who had threatened to leap from a third-floor window was arrested.
